parameters:
Queen Caron: Hehehe, I can't believe we actually managed to
create a dragon.

Queen Caron: Keeping you until today was the right
decision.

Court Magician Eratoma: That is an imperfect dragon. Please
give me some time, but next time I will show you a perfect
one.

Court Magician Eratoma: I can barely control it, at best,
the range of my magic is limited.

Imperial Dark Faction: If that's the case, it would be
meaningless. Queen Caron does not desire something that
would destroy the empire from within.
Queen Caron: Are there any other flaws?

Court Magician Eratoma: I haven't been able to verify its
speed, but because it is imperfect, it will gradually self-
destruct...

Court Magician Eratoma: If the myth is true, it would be
possible to regenerate by absorbing magic power. We should
aim for a place where magic power overflows, a so-called
sacred mountain.

Imperial Dark Faction: We would like to make a
suggestion... The experiment of dragon flight is too
dangerous.

Queen Caron: As long as it can be controlled to a minimum
extent, there will be no damage to the palace where I
reside.

Queen Caron: If they were to burn down villages, we can
send Atu to the battlefield with a just cause.

Queen Caron: If we consider that the war with Tarasa, which
has already restrained Rex, will not happen for a while,
Clea is a bothersome presence.

Queen Caron: A duel between Atu and the dragon would be
ideal. Many soldiers personally follow him, so it would be
troublesome to assassinate him.

Court Magician Eratoma: As expected, Queen Caron! Now,
please give me your orders, where should I teleport to!
Queen Caron: Hmm... Hey, bring me a map.

Queen Caron: Attack the mansion located deep in Alkay
Village, and after that, you may leave the dragon to its own
devices.
Court Magician Eratoma: Understood, Queen Caron.
Imperial Dark Faction: Why that place...?

Queen Caron: The mansion where the man who saved the High
Priest Laoco of the Terios religion resides is located
slightly away from the village, so it is convenient.

Queen Caron: And... hehe, if that Laoco had died, I would
have been able to gain control over the Terios religion.

Queen Caron: Moreover, it will be interesting to see how
far someone without any connections to the nobility or the
Senate can handle the dragon.

Queen Caron: Eratoma, I will spare no expense for your
research. In return, create a dragon that I can control.

Queen Caron: You must create it without fail. Your next
task is to do that.

Court Magician Eratoma: As you wish... For me, researching
dragons is the greatest reward.

That night, the dragon danced in the sky of Fotizona.
Eratoma, upon seeing the flying dragon, naturally shed
tears. He had touched the truth. It's not that it flies
beautifully, but rather, it flies because it is beautiful.

Eratoma had only told one lie to Caron. The control of the
dragon is only possible as long as Eratoma's magic power
remains inside it, and once that magic power is depleted,
all control becomes impossible.

If things go wrong, there might be damage throughout the
entire Fotizona. And even the palace where Caron lives is
not an exception. However, Eratoma still wanted to see the
dragon dancing in the sky.

The dragon attacked the mansion in Archee Village precisely.
The couple who lived there died, but their daughter was the
only survivor.

The girl's name is Clea. Eventually, the girl will embark
on a journey to kill the dragon. With the dragon's scar on
her back, vengeance in her heart, and a great sword in her
hand.
3.イベント後のプレイヤーの位置
